{
  "stem": "14212.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I felt that I have a home to go to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I came there, believe it or not-- the cousin of mine wasn't home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was a big [? seucher ?] and he wasn't home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But his family-- his wife-- had [INAUDIBLE] [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] She picked her hands and said, oh, thank God.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Somebody of you is here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they treated me well but, look, after all I wasn't a-- a kid anymore.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I was a young man.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And over there I found a full house of people from family-- cousins, first cousins, second cousins.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "All day it was about 15 people there from Warsaw, from Radom, from [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The whole family was there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So the next day, I went to a different cousin's house, and I was there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then-- and I lived in Rowne, until in January-- this was the beginning of December.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In January, the Russians started to register people to go to the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For labor-- to work, to live there because here, the conditions were terrible.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All the shuls, all of the public places, were taken from the [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Biegenses ?], from the people who came from the other side, which ran away from the part when Germany took over.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The railroad station-- it's a big beautiful, railroad station-- you couldn't walk down the steps-- every piece was taken by people sitting there, and sleeping-- and doing everything what they needed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was terrible.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, knowing that I have an uncle in Moscow, living before the war-- so I thought, look, maybe I'll go there and it'll ease up a little bit.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I was thinking about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
